<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-05T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-05T06:00:00-05:00" n="833" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d833">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/3999: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Seville</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Seville</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-05T11:00:00+00:00">December 5, 1936—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>General Queipo de Llano promised to inform General Franco of the
                                contents of the Department’s [December?] 3, 5 p.m. which I
                                communicated to him last night. On that occasion he stated Russian
                                merchantmen were flying flags of other countries and on one occasion
                                flew the American flag while in Spanish waters. He stated also that
                                a Russian submarine is known to be operating along the Spanish
                                coast. These comments were offered apparently to convey an idea of
                                the lawless tactics against which they are contending.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bay</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>